                                                Nationality of Nobel Peace =
Prize laureates 1901-2025
                                            </h3><p class=3D"statisticsSlid=
er__desc responsiveText responsiveText--underlinedLinks"></p><p>The United =
States holds the highest number of winners of the Nobel Peace Prize, with 2=
3 winners. The most recent U.S. citizen to win the prize was former Preside=
nt Barack Obama in 2009. The United Kingdom holds the second-highest number=
 of winners with eleven, whereas both Switzerland and UN organizations had =
received ten each. In 2025, the prize was awarded to the Venezuelan politic=
ian and activist Maria Corina Machado for her work promoting democratizatio=
n in Venezuela. The Nobel Peace Prize is awarded annually to people or orga=
nizations who make a substantial commitment to promote peace around the wor=
ld.</p><p></p></div><a href=3D"https://www.statista.com/statistics/1417166/=
